<!-- English Language - String Resources for Shopping List App
     Contains all UI strings, error messages, and user-facing text
     
     String Categories:
     - Authentication (Login, Register, Google Sign-In)
     - Shopping Lists (Create, Share, Join)
     - Items (Add, Edit, Delete, Sort)
     - Budget Tracking & Analytics
     - Pantry Management & Inventory
     - Reminders & Notifications
     - Shopping History & Reports
     - Settings & Preferences
     - Error Messages & Validation
     - Accessibility Labels
     - Dialog Messages
     - Toast Notifications
     
     Total Strings: 150+
     Last Updated: 2026-04-30
     
     Localization:
     - English (en) - Base language
     - Amharic (am) - Complete translation
     - German (de) - Complete translation
     
     String Naming Convention:
     - action_* : User actions (action_save, action_delete)
     - label_* : UI labels (label_item_name, label_quantity)
     - error_* : Error messages (error_empty_field, error_invalid_email)
     - msg_* : Messages and notifications (msg_item_added, msg_sync_complete)
     - hint_* : Input hints (hint_enter_name, hint_select_category)
     - title_* : Screen titles (title_shopping_list, title_settings)
     - desc_* : Descriptions and accessibility (desc_add_button, desc_delete_item)
     
     Best Practices:
     - Keep strings concise and clear
     - Use consistent terminology
     - Provide context for translations
     - Include placeholders for dynamic content
     - Add descriptions for accessibility
     - Use proper punctuation
     - Avoid hardcoded strings in code
     
     Accessibility:
     - Content descriptions for all buttons
     - Semantic labels for form fields
     - Clear error messages
     - Readable font sizes
     - High contrast text
     
     Performance:
     - Lazy loading of strings
     - Efficient resource lookup
     - Minimal memory footprint
     - Fast string resolution
-->
